graphics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">3D = three-dimensional</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=TOF+%3D+time+of+flight&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">TOF = time of flight</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=2D+%3D+two-dimensional&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">2D = two-dimensional</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">MR imaging is an excellent imaging modality for evaluation of patients with right lower quadrant pain and should be strongly considered in those patients in whom use of iodinated contrast media or radiation is not desirable.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Ivan</span> <span property="familyName">Pedrosa</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Radiology, Beth Israel Deaconess Medical Center, Harvard Medical School, 330 Brookline Ave, Boston, MA 02215. Recipient of a Cum Laude award for an education exhibit at the 2005 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received June 7, 2006; revision requested July 19 and received September 13; accepted September 14. N.M.R. receives research support from GE Healthcare (Waukesha, Wis), is on the advisory board of Berlex Laboratories (Wayne, NJ), and is a consultant to CAD Sciences (White Plains, NY); all other authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Pedrosa/Ivan" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con2" property="author" typeof="Person"><div 